ξ 1. 28. grauissimum: to the modern reader it is remarkable that Sen. takes for granted that his mother suffers more from her son's exile than she did from her husband’s death. But the fact that her husband had reached a great age, may have seemed to make his death, as a natural event, no fit subject for sorrow.
